author: Eric Yep
title: Nymex Crude Back in Red, Oil Likely to Stay Volatile
text: 0136 GMT [Dow Jones] Oil futures are mixed in early Asian trade Wednesday, with Brent trading flat and Nymex crude slipping back into negative territory despite China cutting rates late yesterday. Traders say they expect more volatility today, as market sentiment remains weak after U.S. stocks erased gains heading into the close. Oil prices had rebounded in the previous session after Beijing slashed interest rates and flooded its banking system with new liquidity. Late Tuesday, the American Petroleum Institute reported an unexpected 7.3-million-barrel drop in weekly U.S. crude stocks, which should also support oil...
